            "title": "Article 18",
            "node_id": "0010",
            "summary": "This partial document is an annex to an interministerial decree in the Democratic Republic of Congo, dated May 19, 2015. It outlines detailed procedures for telecommunications services. The main points covered are:\n\n1. **Activation Procedure:** A two-step process involving prior identification of the subscriber (postpaid or prepaid) and activation of the number or connection.\n\n2. **Deactivation Procedure:** Distinguishes between \"old\" and \"new\" subscribers based on activation date relative to the decree's signature. It specifies processes for deactivation due to:\n    - Non-identification of old subscribers.\n    - Insufficient identification of old subscribers.\n    These processes involve verification, joint reports, service interruption, and final deactivation, all initiated by a formal request from a competent Authority.\n\n3. **Reactivation Procedure:** Describes the steps for reactivating a number or connection previously deactivated due to lack or insufficiency of identification, including identification after proof of payment, communication to a mixed commission, reactivation, and notification.\n\n4. **Payment of Fees and Penalties:** States that fees and penalties are levied for non-compliance with specific articles of the decree, as recorded by a mixed commission report. These payments must be made to the public treasury according to relevant legislation.\n\nThe document also lists the government officials responsible for executing the decree.",
